olive oil
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 packet fusilli
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet bechamel sauce
½ tin tinned cherry tomatoes
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag parsley
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Half-fill a large saucepan with water, add a generous pinch of salt, then bring to the boil.
• Meanwhile, roughly chop mild chorizo. Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• Cook fusilli in boiling water, over high heat, until ‘al dente’, 12 minutes.
• Reserve some pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for 4 people). Drain fusilli, then return to saucepan.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chorizo and chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Add garlic & herb seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Reduce heat to medium, add bechamel sauce, tinned cherry tomatoes (see ingredients) and a splash of the reserved pasta water and cook until slightly reduced, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, stir through cooked fusilli and baby spinach leaves. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a splash more of pasta water if the mixture looks dry.

• Divide quick creamy cherry tomato, chicken and chorizo fusilli between bowls.
• Sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese and tear over parsley to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling the cheese on top.